Cameroon’s Average Cocoa Export Price Declined 7.2% Last Week, Board Says

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-08-23T11:52:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-23/cameroon-s-average-cocoa-export-price-declined-7-2-last-week-board-says.html
The average price of cocoa exports
from Cameroon’s main port of Douala declined 7.2 percent in the
week to yesterday, the country’s Cocoa and Coffee Board said.  The price fell to 1,318  CFA francs  a kilogram (2.2
pounds)from 1,420 francs a week earlier, according to data from
the board sent in a mobile-phone text message today.  Cameroon is  Africa ’s fourth-biggest producer of the crop
after  Ivory Coast ,  Ghana  and  Nigeria .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde at 
 plukong@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Gordon Bell  at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  